SIMPLE: sophistry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sophistry
<hw>Soph"ist*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sophistrie</ets>, OF. <ets>sophisterie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The art or process of reasoning; logic.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The practice of a sophist; fallacious reasoning;
reasoning sound in appearance only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The juggle of <qex>sophistry</qex> consists, for the most part, in
usig a word in one sense in the premise, and in another sense in the
conclusion.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Fallacy</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sophomore</ent>⟦br⟧
